Commentary Text: Sandeep Sharma to Dhoni, no run, nearly an absolute screamer from Sandeep! Would have made it straight into the top IPL catches of all time, had he held on. Shortish and stuck off the pitch as Dhoni looked to work across the line. Popped a leading edge well wide of Sandeep who dived one-handed to his left, almost aeroplane-like but it didn't stick. Commentary Text: Sandeep Sharma to Sam Curran, out Bowled!! It's always a great sight to see a bowler beat a batsman's defence and hit the poles. Sandeep Sharma came round the wicket, angled this good length delivery in and then got it to move away, Curran plays inside the line and misses completely, top of leg stump and he's got both the openers. 2.4-0-6-2 thus far! Wow! Not quite the sample size CSK would have wanted with the Curran experiment but that Khaleel over makes it 50-50. Definitely not a bad start. Sam Curran b Sandeep Sharma 31(21) [4s-3 6s-2]
